The paper discusses the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) for intrusion detection in the Internet of Things (IoT), which is a topic related to cybersecurity (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also focuses on the distributed nature of the IoT and proposes a fully distributed IDS, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses GANs to detect anomalous behavior, which is a common application of deep learning (cs.AI).
